description:
When a user who does not have the Access Security Keywords privilege expands an autofill which includes security masked keywords, the security masked keywords are not handled properly.In import: The "masked" value is saved as the value. For example, if a SSN is security masked to display as XXX-XX-XXXX, and the autofill keyset has a value of 555-00-5555, when the under privileged user expands that keyset a value of "XXX-XX-XXXX" will be saved on the document.In re-index: The security masked keywords are not updated to the keyset values. For example, a document was imported by a privileged user and the security masked keyword was populated with Sandy Jones' social security number. An under privileged user then re-indexes the document, expanding the keyset associated with Mark Parker. The non-masked keywords will all be saved with Mark's information, but the masked social security number will still be Sandy's social security number.As a part of this work, support should be added for security masked read-only Processing File Name Keywords being populated in the Import keyword panel (see 

).This issue also exists in Web Client and should be handled as a part of 

, including handling in both PerformAutofillKeysetExpansion and SwitchDocumentType.

